Quick Comparison: return vs yield
Feature return (Normal Function)                       yield (Generator Function)
Execution: Terminates the function immediately.         Pauses the function and saves state.
State Retention: Destroys all local variables.          Retains local variables for the next call.
Data Delivery: Sends back a single object/entire list.   Sends back a continuous stream of elements.
Memory Footprint: High (scales with dataset size).        Extremely low (constant overhead)




